page.title: 01AROUND OUTWOOD SURREY
page.content: Outwood is the main point of interest in this area as a village. It has a post office, a pub, butcher and church most noteable the oldest working windmill. The poulation is just over 300 and large areas of outwood are National Trust. The surrounding area is farmland, some cultivated fields and others enclosed for rough grazing. the village of Horne is included in this area consists of mostly farmland, but a small amount of manufacturing works. Transport consists of a Post Bus through Outwood. People living here either work on the farms, a few in industry and many work out of the area. Schools in this area have now closed, and children travel out to them.
